Step-by-step reasoning:
The user wants to set the Patio Fan-Motor to medium speed.

From the device structure, the Patio Fan-Motor accepts the command "On" [DON] with a parameter indicating the speed level.
The valid speed parameters are Off [0], Low [25], Medium [75], and High [100].

To set the fan to medium speed, we send the command "On" with parameter value 75 (Medium speed).

No conditions are specified, so this is a direct action.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Set Patio Fan-Motor to Medium Speed",
    "action": {
      "device": "Patio Fan-Motor",
      "command": "On",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "",
          "value": 75,
          "uom": "percent",
          "precision": 0
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
